"then, is to make an initial assessment of the situation. Mobile health units are not an assessment strategy, for assessments generate too many expectations on the part of the population. It is important to have thorough knowledge of the various actors involved, as it is they who will make it possible to apply modes of action other than substitution. \n# What is important ? The initial assessment will bring into focus a set of problems, some of them more important than others. The task here is to identify the problems of highest priority. In dealing with the various partners, actors and authorities, three questions must constantly be asked: what is known, what can be done and what will be done?"